&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a motivated, enthusiastic and responsible Health Visitor SCPHN to work within our 0-19 service., who is passionate about improving the outcomes for children, young people and families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will be to deliver the Healthy Child Programme as part of our one team approach within the Gateshead 0-19 Children&#39;s Service. Planning, delivering and evaluating an efficient and cost effective service for an identified population. You will be delivering the National and Local Public Health agendas in response to identified health and social need. You will be delivering services as part of the wider Integrated team and thus will be working alongside our partner agencies in Children’s services to deliver effective safeguarding of children.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information please contact Christine Mills - Service Manager&lt;/p&gt;
